                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>No 46 South St</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                <date>March 8<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1858</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I duly received your returned favor<lb/> of <date>3<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >rd</hi></date> inst. the package of Books also came safely<lb/> to hand and\n                have been distributed as per directions.<lb/> I have an understanding with\n                    <add>?</add> to return<lb/> to me any Occidents not delivered. They for now<lb/>\n                have been returned to him by his carriers. No delay<lb/> occurred this time in\n                distributing the work and I<lb/> trust hereafter all will go on smoothly &amp;\n                without<lb/> delay.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have the package of Books from <placeName>Charleston</placeName>,\n                it<lb/> was with <persName>H. Barillien</persName>. Book Seller <placeName>No. 29\n                    Broadway</placeName>.<lb/> If I do not have an opportunity to send it on\n                privately<lb/> within a few days, I will send it by express.<lb/> I have not yet\n                seen <persName>B. Cohen</persName> but will do so the first<lb/> time I go that way,\n                and collect your bill against him<lb/> It affords now much pleasure to furnish you\n                with a<lb/> letter of introduction to <persName>Mr Lane</persName> of the Ledger\n                (which<lb/> letter I enclose) and hope it may be of service to you.<lb/> You will\n                find, <persName>Mr Lane</persName> a very clean man, although plain<lb/> and old\n                fashioned, but not, as learned as your goodself<lb/> He is no bigot on Religious\n                matters; and I think feels disposed<lb/> to let even <add>?</add> enjoy their own\n                opinions on that subject.<lb/> I have not seen the articles you refer to, as\n                published</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3t72822s/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
