                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3t72822s/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>under dates of <date>18<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> &amp; <date>24<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >th</hi> Feby</date>. as I seldom see the<lb/> Ledger. I hope you will soon\n                succeed in silencing<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">all</hi> your foes.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Please say to <persName>Mr Cozens</persName> the family left by\n                    <persName>Mr Thorp</persName><lb/> are getting along very comfortably\n                    <del>and</del> the children by<lb/> his first wife are all married except\n                    <persName>Delia</persName>, the youngest<lb/> and all remain with their step\n                mother except <persName>Charlotte</persName><lb/> &amp;\n                <persName>Charles</persName>. <persName>Charlotte</persName> did not marry will no a\n                worldly<lb/> point and has now got ahead <del>any</del> I have seen her<lb/> but\n                once for 3 or 9 years &amp; then she looked old &amp; careless<lb/> she has I\n                believe only one child, a Daughter. <persName>Charles</persName><lb/> has been\n                married several years, but has no children<lb/> having lost by death the only he\n                ever had; last summer<lb/> he got possession of his fathers Stove &amp; Stock at the\n                sale of his<lb/> effects for a mere song and is now carrying on the<lb/> stove\n                business with the assistance of <persName>Charlottes</persName> Husband<lb/> I do\n                not think he will ever make a rich man—<lb/>\n                <persName>Athinaus<add>?</add></persName> is married to a very good, young man\n                and<lb/> is doing very well, she has one child only, a Boy.<lb/>\n                <persName>Sarah</persName> was married on <date>Thursday</date> last, to a man<lb/>\n                who is some 10 or 12 years her senior, by profession a Bookkeeper<lb/> on a\n                    <sic>sallary</sic> of $1200 pr an but said to be an excellent man<lb/>\n                <persName>Sarah</persName> is an excellent girl and was very much beloved by\n                her<lb/> step mother. <persName>Delia</persName> is also a good girl and in manner\n                &amp;<lb/> appearance decidedly the flower of the family. She is very<lb/> lady like\n                &amp; easy in her manners &amp; has been well educated<lb/>\n                <persName>Mrs Thorp</persName> deserves great credit for the care she has taken<lb/>\n                of the family and for the manner in which she has brought</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3t72822s/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
